anging the /assist function back to it's original (read crappy) design?  I play a necro, so the assist helps me out a lot when I want to med, and want to target incoming mob for sending pet in ASAP, so by changing it to the old style (having to wait until the person is attacking said mob) I lose a couple of rounds my pet could be helping out.<br>
<br>
On a side note I tested this with a ranger friend of mine (OK.. so it'll offend you RP'ers out there.. get over it! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )and when he does ranged attacks to pull, I can't /assist him.  Is this part of the normal function, I thought I read somewhere that ranged attacks are considered engaged and I should be able to target said mob.<br>
<br>
Ideas, comments, flames, satire? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualvimar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alvimar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 344<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/13/01 8:42:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /Assist and changes</span><hr size=1> I think one of the main reasons they switched back involved people assisting too early in a pull and breaking mez in a raid setting.  I personally liked the assist to target whether they were attacking or not but there were down sides, mainly from the same folks who don't listen when someone tells them to back off in a raid. <p><FONT face="Comic Sans MS" size="2" font color=#8A2BE2>Bristlebane's best to you all,<br>
